<TITLE> CA inspects water supply plant at Sharankhola </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bagerhat, Nov 27 (bdnews24.com)  Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed Tuesday visited inspected an LGED water treatment plant in Sharankhola, one of the worst cyclone-ravaged areas of the south. To address the acute water scarcity in the aftermath of Cyclone Sidr, the Local Government Engineering Department has built a new water treatment plant in the area. Fakhruddin flew in by helicopter to visit the plant and distribute warm cloths among the cyclone survivors. The interim government head directed government officials to develop better coordination among agencies to bolster relief distribution. He stressed the need to urgently repair and rebuild all damaged educational institutions and roads. bdnews24.
